For in Rome the longest days and nights reach a length some- thing greater than 15 equinoctial hours, as conversely the shortest fall a little short of 93 in Alexandria on the other hand the longest are of 14 h. the shortest of 10. He then who is released from service at sunset on the shortest days and longest nights‚ is able both to rub himself at leisure and to bathe and sleep sufficiently. And even on the longest days there is no one who may not do so in some moderate degree: I at any rate never knew any one who was so unfortunate. For Antoninus, who of all the emperors known to us was most devoted to the care of his body, entered the palaestra on the short days at sun-set, on the lonyest at the ninth, or at latest at the tenth hour.
